            <title>[NET-483] Base64.encodeBase64(byte[], boolean, boolean, int) does not calculate output size correctly for unchunked output</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-483</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The method Base64.encodeBase64(byte[] binaryData, boolean isChunked, boolean urlSafe, int maxResultSize) fails to calculate the output size correctly for unchunked output.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because it assumes all output is chunked.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
